00:06:42,606 --> 00:06:44,998
because they're so tiny that they sneak by.

141
00:06:44,998 --> 00:06:46,917
But this happens pretty slowly

142
00:06:46,917 --> 00:06:49,323
because the hydrophobic region still

143
00:06:49,323 --> 00:06:50,865
doesn't like having water in there.

144
00:06:50,865 --> 00:06:53,995
So, if we have small, polar molecules,

145
00:06:53,995 --> 00:06:55,081
what about something that is large

146
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:59,139
but nonpolar, like benzene?

147
00:06:59,139 --> 00:07:02,076
Benzene can actually pass through the cell membrane.

148
00:07:02,076 --> 00:07:04,262
Even though it's large, it's non-polar,

149
00:07:04,262 --> 00:07:07,662
so it's going to get along well with the hydrophobic region,

150
00:07:07,662 --> 00:07:12,279
but it's going to pass through very slowly.

151
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:14,506
As a fun fact, benzene used to be used

152
00:07:14,506 --> 00:07:18,405
in labs for researchers to wash their hands.

153
