172
00:08:14,139 --> 00:08:15,732
In summary, our cell membrane

173
00:08:15,732 --> 00:08:17,387
protects our cell

174
00:08:17,387 --> 00:08:19,489
and determines what enters and leaves,

175
00:08:19,489 --> 00:08:21,936
a property that we call semi-permeability.

176
00:08:21,936 --> 00:08:24,275
This cell membrane is made up of

177
00:08:24,275 --> 00:08:27,174
a bunch of phospholipids put together.

178
00:08:27,174 --> 00:08:31,322
Since our cell membrane has a large hydrophobic region,

179
00:08:31,322 --> 00:08:33,988
it prefers non-polar molecules,

180
00:08:33,988 --> 00:08:37,491
and since these phospholipids are packed so closely,

181
00:08:37,491 --> 00:08:41,743
the cell membrane also prefers small molecules to pass through.

182
00:08:41,743 --> 00:08:43,975
The cell membrane is semi-permeable,

183
00:08:43,975 --> 00:08:46,821
allowing generally small and non-polar

184
00:08:46,821 --> 00:08:49,866
molecules to pass through.
